2026-04-20 19:08:33 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control module comparator component (IC or discrete)', 'Comparator reference voltage network (including any reference voltage divider/resistors)'] hypothesis_explanation='The key symptoms are: the system is unstable/oscillating, both potentiometer wipers are floating despite there being no track or assembly fault detected, and the circuit simulation does not converge. The extensive testing indicates the physical assembly (potentiometers, tracks, connectors) is intact. The only plausible root cause left is a fault within the comparator circuitry itself or the reference voltage network that sets the threshold. This could mean a missing or internally open resistor in the reference divider, or an internal disconnection/open-circuit within the comparator IC or discrete components, causing its high-impedance input(s) to float. These floating nodes could explain why potentiometer settings have no effect and why the relay oscillates. Thus, the essential fault is either a bad comparator or its voltage reference network.'
